---
/**
 * /magpie/faq — common questions.
 *
 * Grouped into: privacy, pricing, what-it-isn't, setup, destinations,
 * agents, roadmap. Each question is a plain <details> so it's
 * print-friendly + scriptable.
 */

import BlockLayout from '../../layouts/BlockLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    section: 'Privacy & data',
    items: [
      {
        q: 'Does Magpie send my clipboard anywhere?',
        a: "No. Your clipboard lives in a local SQLite database in ~/Library/Application Support/Magpie/clipboard.sqlite. Nothing is sent to any server unless you explicitly push or broadcast a clip. We built Magpie because we wanted that to be true for ourselves."
      },
      {
        q: 'Where are my tokens stored?',
        a: "In your macOS Keychain, scoped per publisher (e.g. com.good-feels.magpie.publisher/mastodon/access_token). Same security as Safari passwords. Access requires your login — if someone can read that Keychain, they already have root on your Mac."
      },
      {
        q: 'What about analytics?',
        a: "Magpie sends non-content telemetry to Mixpanel: publish_attempted, publish_outcome, composer_opened, with bucketed values (text-length bucket, duration-ms bucket, error category). No clip contents. No titles. No user identifiers beyond an install-level anonymous ID. Toggle off in Preferences → General → Analytics."
      },
      {
        q: 'What does the cloud scheduler send?',
        a: "Only what you schedule to broadcast at a future time, and only when you opt into cloud scheduling. Credentials for non-pointcast destinations travel in an AES-GCM-256 envelope that the worker CAN'T decrypt — only your local Magpie can open them. The worker stores + forwards; the client fans out."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'Pricing & license',
    items: [
      {
        q: 'How much does Magpie cost?',
        a: "Free. MIT licensed. No accounts, no subscriptions, no upsells."
      },
      {
        q: 'Will there be a paid tier?',
        a: "Maybe a hosted-scheduler tier someday that handles server-side credential forwarding for heavy schedulers. The core clipboard + broadcast will always be free."
      },
      {
        q: 'Can I use Magpie commercially?',
        a: "Yes. MIT is MIT."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'What it is / isn\'t',
    items: [
      {
        q: "Is Magpie a Hootsuite competitor?",
        a: "Not really. Hootsuite assumes you sit in their composer. Magpie inverts that — you capture where you already are, then broadcast. Also Hootsuite is Web2-only; Magpie is Web2 + Web3 (Farcaster, bitchat, Zora, Objkt) + PointCast."
      },
      {
        q: 'Why macOS only?',
        a: "Native menu-bar integration is the whole UX premise. Once that's solid, iOS + Windows become possible — iOS especially, since the Mac version's HTTP peer-node already means phones can reach it on LAN."
      },
      {
        q: 'Is this open source?',
        a: "Yes — github.com/Good-Feels/magpie. All eleven adapters, the composer, the scheduler, the cloud worker, the tutorial pages, the CLI, everything."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'Setup',
    items: [
      {
        q: 'What do I need to install?',
        a: "A .dmg from github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/releases. Drag to /Applications. First launch asks for clipboard access."
      },
      {
        q: 'Do I need a PointCast account?',
        a: "No. Magpie works standalone as a clipboard manager. PointCast is the default destination because it's unauthed and the canonical home for the block-type taxonomy, but you can use Magpie without ever posting there."
      },
      {
        q: 'Which destinations need what?',
        a: "PointCast: nothing. Mastodon: instance + access token. Farcaster: Neynar API key + approved signer. Bluesky: handle + app password. Twitter/LinkedIn: OAuth 2.0 via browser. bitchat: Nostr nsec + relay list. Zora/Objkt: wallet (Tezos key native; EVM needs secp256k1 — see v1.0 notes). Instagram: Meta Business OAuth. OpenSea: EVM wallet + API key."
      },
      {
        q: 'Where do I get a Pinata JWT?',
        a: "app.pinata.cloud — free tier covers casual use. Paste the JWT in Preferences → IPFS. Magpie uses it to auto-stage local images for Farcaster embeds and (v1.1) Zora/Objkt mint metadata."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'Destinations',
    items: [
      {
        q: "Why include bitchat?",
        a: "bitchat's internet transport is Nostr. Magpie broadcasts a NIP-01 kind-1 event to a configurable relay pool; any bitchat client subscribed to those relays picks it up. Once on the mesh, delivery propagates BLE when peers bridge. It's the most local-first destination in the list."
      },
      {
        q: 'How does threading work?',
        a: "Mastodon, Twitter, Bluesky, Farcaster, bitchat all support reply-chains. Drafts longer than the destination's char limit auto-split with (n/m) tags, linked via the platform's native reply mechanism."
      },
      {
        q: 'Can I tweak copy per platform?',
        a: "Yes. In the composer, click the chevron on any selected destination to open an override editor — populated with what the adapter would send by default. Your platform-specific variant replaces it."
      },
      {
        q: 'What about video / audio?',
        a: "v1.0 is image-only. Video + audio attachments land in v1.1. The MediaAttachment type already reserves .video and .audio cases."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'Agents',
    items: [
      {
        q: 'How does the peer-node API work?',
        a: "When you turn on 'Serve local web UI' in Preferences → PointCast, Magpie runs an HTTP server on 127.0.0.1:38473. GET /clips.json lists clips. POST /broadcast fans out. GET /summary returns a 30-day recap. Full API at /magpie.json — it's the agent-discovery manifest."
      },
      {
        q: 'Can Claude/ChatGPT publish through Magpie?',
        a: "Yes. Any agent that can make HTTP requests to localhost can read clips + trigger broadcasts. The hosted /magpie/activity page does exactly that — it's client-side JS fetching your peer node."
      },
      {
        q: "Do you have an MCP server?",
        a: "Not yet — the peer-node HTTP API is the de facto equivalent. An MCP wrapper is a reasonable v1.1 ship if the request comes up."
      },
    ]
  },
  {
    section: 'Roadmap',
    items: [
      {
        q: 'What shipped in v1.0?',
        a: "Everything in /magpie/changelog. Highlights: 11 destinations, 3 native wallet signers, 6 composer presets, reach dashboard, cloud scheduler with encrypted credential forwarding, interactive tour + long-form guide."
      },
      {
        q: "What's in v1.1?",
        a: "Real mint submission paths (Zora Base RPC, Tezos RPC + Michelson for Objkt), Instagram Graph API, OpenSea Seaport, video attachments, hardware wallet bridges (Beacon + WalletConnect)."
      },
      {
        q: 'Feature request?',
        a: "File an issue at github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/issues. Or post to PointCast with #magpie — the sprint-pick queue reads public asks."
      },
    ]
  },
];
---

<BlockLayout
  channelCode="FD"
  blockType="READ"
  title="Magpie · FAQ"
  description="Common questions about Magpie — privacy, pricing, setup, agents."
  pageTitle="Magpie FAQ"
>
  <article class="mgq-root">
    <header class="mgq-head">
      <p class="mgq-kicker">frequently asked</p>
      <h1 class="mgq-title">Questions we've heard.</h1>
      <p class="mgq-dek">
        If something isn't covered, ping
        <a href="https://github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/issues">GitHub issues</a>
        or <a href="https://pointcast.xyz">pointcast.xyz</a>.
      </p>
    </header>

    {faqs.map((group) => (
      <section class="mgq-group">
        <h2>{group.section}</h2>
        <div class="mgq-items">
          {group.items.map((item) => (
            <details class="mgq-item">
              <summary>{item.q}</summary>
              <p>{item.a}</p>
            </details>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    ))}

    <footer class="mgq-foot">
      <a href="/magpie/launch">← back to launch</a>
      <a href="/magpie/guide">full guide →</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BlockLayout>

<style>
  :root {
    --mg-paper: #EFE8D2;
    --mg-paper-tint: #E7DFC4;
    --mg-card: #FAF5E0;
    --mg-rule: #C8B98E;
    --mg-rule-soft: #E0D6B6;
    --mg-ink: #1E1C14;
    --mg-ink-soft: #5A544A;
    --mg-ink-mute: #8A8273;
    --mg-moss: #3E5940;
    --mg-clay: #AE6A38;
    --mg-bronze: #7E5A2A;
    --mg-display: Georgia, 'Iowan Old Style', serif;
    --mg-mono: ui-monospace, 'IBM Plex Mono', 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
  }

  .mgq-root {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 60px;
    background: var(--mg-paper);
    color: var(--mg-ink);
    font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .mgq-head { margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .mgq-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .mgq-title {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 40px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
  }
  .mgq-dek {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mgq-dek a { color: var(--mg-bronze); }

  .mgq-group { margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .mgq-group h2 {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 22px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: var(--mg-moss);
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .mgq-items { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
  .mgq-item {
    background: var(--mg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--mg-rule-soft);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    transition: border-color 180ms;
  }
  .mgq-item[open] {
    border-color: var(--mg-rule);
  }
  .mgq-item summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .mgq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .mgq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
    font-weight: 700;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
  }
  .mgq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
  .mgq-item p {
    margin: 10px 0 2px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .mgq-foot {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule);
    margin-top: 20px;
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  }
  .mgq-foot a {
    color: var(--mg-bronze);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .mgq-foot a:hover { color: var(--mg-clay); }

  @media print {
    .mgq-item { break-inside: avoid; }
    .mgq-item[open] summary::after { content: ''; }
    .mgq-item p { display: block !important; }
    details > summary { list-style: none; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .mgq-title { font-size: 28px; }
  }
</style>
